{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784377948550,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_ye35xfBAmSdGyfHUqIozgHSN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"buildLineageCommand|cli-opencode|SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID|AI_SESSION_CHILD","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs"},"output":"Found 13 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/codex-dispatch.cjs:\n  Line 129:     env: { ...process.env, AI_SESSION_CHILD: '1' },\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:\n  Line 152:         'cli-opencode': ['headless command execution through YAML-owned audited dispatch only'],\n\n  Line 350:         'cli-opencode': ['headless command execution through YAML-owned audited dispatch only'],\n\n  Line 451:         'cli-opencode': ['headless command execution through YAML-owned audited dispatch only'],\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:\n  Line 440:   'cli-opencode': 'SPECKIT_OPENCODE_STATE_DIR',\n\n  Line 1012:   const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n\n  Line 1382: function buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, resolvedSandbox, resolvedPermission, options = {}) {\n\n  Line 1444:   if (kind === 'cli-opencode') {\n\n  Line 1468:         `FATAL WARN: lineage ${lineage.label || '(cli-opencode)'} runs with --dangerously-skip-permissions. `\n\n  Line 1741:       const { command, args: cmdArgs, input } = buildLineageCommand(\n\n  Line 1766:         SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID: lineage.label,\n\n  Line 1777:       const inheritedLineageId = process.env.SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID;\n\n  Line 1998:   buildLineageCommand,\n","metadata":{"matches":13,"truncated":false},"title":"buildLineageCommand|cli-opencode|SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID|AI_SESSION_CHILD","time":{"start":1784377948532,"end":1784377948549}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dd1e7cfd9f5a389016a5b725c74a88191b8f3fbdeec6096f7"}},"id":"prt_f7536b970001tAuXLjfsc0Xdm1","sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","messageID":"msg_f7536701f001wx9UQplIG4gjnY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784377948556,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fPY7ex2ae2enkEINkvjcr5EY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Fan-out loop dispatch\"\n3: description: \"Opt-in fan-out dispatch layer in the research loop: step_resolve_artifact_root artifact-dir override branch, step_fanout_spawn (CLI pool + native sequential agent dispatch), and step_fanout_merge at the top of phase_synthesis. Single-executor path unchanged.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"fan-out loop dispatch\"\n6:   - \"fanout dispatch\"\n7:   - \"step_fanout_spawn\"\n8:   - \"parallel lineage execution\"\n9:   - \"multi-executor research\"\n10: version: 1.14.0.4\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Fan-out loop dispatch\n14: \n15: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: When `config.fanout` is present, three new YAML steps activate in the research loop.\n22: \n23: **`step_resolve_artifact_root`** gains a `branch_on: config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`\n24: branch. When the override is present (set by a lineage subprocess), `artifact_dir` is bound\n25: directly. When absent (single-executor mode), the `if_absent` branch runs the byte-identical\n26: original `resolveArtifactRoot` command — zero behavior change for single-executor runs.\n27: \n28: **`step_fanout_spawn`** (`skip_when: config.fanout is absent`) spawns CLI lineages via\n29: `fanout-run.cjs` (pool-capped headless subprocesses) and dispatches native lineages as\n30: sequential `agent: deep-research` runs with per-lineage isolated artifact dirs. When\n31: complete, control jumps directly to `phase_synthesis`, skipping `phase_init` and\n32: `phase_main_loop`.\n33: \n34: **`step_fanout_merge`** (`skip_when: config.fanout is absent`) sits at the top of\n35: `phase_synthesis`. It calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type research` to produce a\n36: consolidated `deep-research-findings-registry.json` from all lineage registries before the\n37: existing `step_compile_research` runs.\n38: \n39: ### Why This Matters\n40: \n41: These three YAML steps are the sole integration point between the research loop and the\n42: fan-out runtime primitives. If any drift or lose their `skip_when` guard, single-executor\n43: behavior breaks or lineage isolation fails.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n48: \n49: Fully shipped in both `deep_research_auto.yaml` and `confirm.yaml`. Parity\n50: gate: `if_absent` branch is byte-identical to the original command; `skip_when` guards\n51: ensure zero behavioral change for single-executor mode. Full vitest suite (197/197) confirms\n52: no single-executor regression. Command surface: `--executor` (repeatable, with\n53: `--model/--count/--label/--iters`), `--executors <json>` escape hatch, `--concurrency N`.\n54: Default policy: 0–1 executor → `config.executor`; 2+ / `--executors` / `count>1` →\n55: `config.fanout`.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n60: \n61: ### Implementation\n62: \n63: | File | Role |\n64: |---|---|\n65: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | `step_resolve_artifact_root` (if_present/if_absent branches), `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge` |\n66: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` | Same steps (confirm variant) |\n67: | `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md` | `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flag docs, default policy, fan-out examples |\n68: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | CLI lineage pool driver called by `step_fanout_spawn_cli` |\n69: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Cross-lineage merger called by `step_fanout_merge` |\n70: \n71: ### Validation\n72: \n73: | File | Role |\n74: |---|---|\n75: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | Pool dispatch + lineage dir isolation |\n76: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | Research registry dedup + attribution |\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n81: \n82: - Group: Loop Lifecycle\n83: - Catalog source: `feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md`\n84: - Primary source files: `deep_research_auto.yaml`, `research.md`\n85: Related references:\n86: - [resource-map-emission.md](../loop_lifecycle/resource_map_emission.md) — Resource Map Emission\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out loop dispatch\"\ndescription: \"Opt-in fan-out dispatch layer in the research loop: step_resolve_artifact_root artifact-dir override branch, step_fanout_spawn (CLI pool + native sequential agent dispatch), and step_fanout_merge at the top of phase_synthesis. Single-executor path unchanged.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fan-out loop dispatch\"\n  - \"fanout dispatch\"\n  - \"step_fanout_spawn\"\n  - \"parallel lineage execution\"\n  - \"multi-executor research\"\nversion: 1.14.0.4\n---\n\n# Fan-out loop dispatch\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out loop dispatch\"\ndescription: \"Opt-in fan-out dispatch layer in the research loop: step_resolve_artifact_root artifact-dir override branch, step_fanout_spawn (CLI pool + native sequential agent dispatch), and step_fanout_merge at the top of phase_synthesis. Single-executor path unchanged.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fan-out loop dispatch\"\n  - \"fanout dispatch\"\n  - \"step_fanout_spawn\"\n  - \"parallel lineage execution\"\n  - \"multi-executor research\"\nversion: 1.14.0.4\n---\n\n# Fan-out loop dispatch\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nWhen `config.fanout` is present, three new YAML steps activate in the research loop.\n\n**`step_resolve_artifact_root`** gains a `branch_on: config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`\nbranch. When the override is present (set by a lineage subprocess), `artifact_dir` is bound\ndirectly. When absent (single-executor mode), the `if_absent` branch runs the byte-identical\noriginal `resolveArtifactRoot` command — zero behavior change for single-executor runs.\n\n**`step_fanout_spawn`** (`skip_when: config.fanout is absent`) spawns CLI lineages via\n`fanout-run.cjs` (pool-capped headless subprocesses) and dispatches native lineages as\nsequential `agent: deep-research` runs with per-lineage isolated artifact dirs. When\ncomplete, control jumps directly to `phase_synthesis`, skipping `phase_init` and\n`phase_main_loop`.\n\n**`step_fanout_merge`** (`skip_when: config.fanout is absent`) sits at the top of\n`phase_synthesis`. It calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type research` to produce a\nconsolidated `deep-research-findings-registry.json` from all lineage registries before the\nexisting `step_compile_research` runs.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThese three YAML steps are the sole integration point between the research loop and the\nfan-out runtime primitives. If any drift or lose their `skip_when` guard, single-executor\nbehavior breaks or lineage isolation fails.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\nFully shipped in both `deep_research_auto.yaml` and `confirm.yaml`. Parity\ngate: `if_absent` branch is byte-identical to the original command; `skip_when` guards\nensure zero behavioral change for single-executor mode. Full vitest suite (197/197) confirms\nno single-executor regression. Command surface: `--executor` (repeatable, with\n`--model/--count/--label/--iters`), `--executors <json>` escape hatch, `--concurrency N`.\nDefault policy: 0–1 executor → `config.executor`; 2+ / `--executors` / `count>1` →\n`config.fanout`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | `step_resolve_artifact_root` (if_present/if_absent branches), `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge` |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` | Same steps (confirm variant) |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md` | `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flag docs, default policy, fan-out examples |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | CLI lineage pool driver called by `step_fanout_spawn_cli` |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Cross-lineage merger called by `step_fanout_merge` |\n\n### Validation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | Pool dispatch + lineage dir isolation |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | Research registry dedup + attribution |\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: Loop Lifecycle\n- Catalog source: `feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md`\n- Primary source files: `deep_research_auto.yaml`, `research.md`\nRelated references:\n- [resource-map-emission.md](../loop_lifecycle/resource_map_emission.md) — Resource Map Emission","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":86,"totalLines":86,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature_catalog/loop_lifecycle/fanout_dispatch.md","time":{"start":1784377948518,"end":1784377948553}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dd1e7cfd9f5a389016a5b725c74848191afc6fc51b0c40df4"}},"id":"prt_f7536b93e001DA63BpJP12UZ2s","sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","messageID":"msg_f7536701f001wx9UQplIG4gjnY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784377948556,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pBsx72u8C5mHeX8ha6PnByqo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1780,"limit":170},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1780:       if (\n1781:         isInsideFanoutLineage\n1782:         && detectSameKindFromStack(process.env[CLI_DISPATCH_STACK_ENV], lineage.kind)\n1783:       ) {\n1784:         throw new Error(\n1785:           `recursive ${lineage.kind} dispatch blocked for lineage ${lineage.label}: ${lineage.kind} already on ${CLI_DISPATCH_STACK_ENV}`,\n1786:         );\n1787:       }\n1788: \n1789:       // Stamp the dispatch stack with this lineage's executor kind so a seat that\n1790:       // tries to recursively launch the same kind is detectable by the runtime\n1791:       // recursion guard (detectSameKindFromStack reads SPECKIT_CLI_DISPATCH_STACK).\n1792:       // buildExecutorDispatchEnv filters the parent env to the per-kind allowlist,\n1793:       // so the SPECKIT_* lineage/state-dir keys are applied AFTER the filter to\n1794:       // preserve the per-replica lockfile isolation they provide.\n1795:       const dispatchEnv = { ...buildExecutorDispatchEnv(lineage, process.env), ...extraEnv };\n1796: \n1797:       const timeoutMs = computeLineageTimeoutMs(lineage, lineageTimeoutHoursOverride);\n1798:       let lastLineageEventAtMs = Date.now();\n1799:       const markLineageEvent = () => {\n1800:         lastLineageEventAtMs = Date.now();\n1801:       };\n1802:       const stopStallWatchdog = startLineageStallWatchdog({\n1803:         thresholdMs: stallWatchdogMs,\n1804:         label: lineage.label,\n1805:         ledgerPath,\n1806:         getLastEventAtMs: () => lastLineageEventAtMs,\n1807:         getGauges: () => latestGauges,\n1808:       });\n1809: \n1810:       const stopProgressHeartbeat = startLineageProgressHeartbeat({\n1811:         cadenceMs: progressHeartbeatMs,\n1812:         label: lineage.label,\n1813:         ledgerPath,\n1814:         getGauges: () => latestGauges,\n1815:       });\n1816:       let result;\n1817:       try {\n1818:         result = await runLineageProcess(command, cmdArgs, {\n1819:           cwd: process.cwd(),\n1820:           timeoutMs,\n1821:           env: dispatchEnv,\n1822:           maxBuffer: 20 * 1024 * 1024,\n1823:           abortSignal: context.signal,\n1824:           onOutput: markLineageEvent,\n1825:           onSpawn: ({ pid }) => {\n1826:             lineageProcessLiveness.set(livenessKey, { alive: true, pid });\n1827:           },\n1828:           onExit: ({ pid, exitedAtMs }) => {\n1829:             lineageProcessLiveness.set(livenessKey, { alive: false, pid, exitedAtMs });\n1830:           },\n1831:           ...(typeof input === 'string' ? { input } : {}),\n1832:         });\n1833:       } finally {\n1834:         stopProgressHeartbeat();\n1835:         stopStallWatchdog();\n1836:       }\n1837: \n1838:       // Save subprocess stdout for salvage sweep (write failures in weak CLI executors).\n1839:       const logsDir = path.join(lineageDir, 'logs');\n1840:       fs.mkdirSync(logsDir, { recursive: true });\n1841:       const savedStdout = typeof result.stdout === 'string' ? result.stdout : '';\n1842:       fs.writeFileSync(path.join(logsDir, 'fanout-lineage.out'), savedStdout, 'utf8');\n1843: \n1844:       // Recover missing iteration files from captured stdout when possible. Runs\n1845:       // BEFORE the failure throw below so iteration recovery is never lost.\n1846:       const salvage = runSalvageSweep(lineageDir, loopType, savedStdout);\n1847:       const slotAccounting = buildSlotAccounting(hrStart, slotIntervalMs);\