ld the 1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus the design-mcp-open-design transport?\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-18T12:35:15Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/.reducer-spec\",\"targetSpecFolder\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"folder_state\":\"fanout-lineage-isolated\",\"normalized_topic\":\"global utilization of the sk-design styles library across non-md-generator modes and open design\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md\",\"mutation\":\"skipped\",\"reason\":\"Detached lineage write boundary forbids writes outside the lineage artifact directory.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:35:15Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+---\n+title: \"Deep Research Strategy: global sk-design styles utilization\"\n+description: \"Detached-lineage strategy for mode-specific utilization of the 1,290-style corpus beyond the baseline retrieval pipeline.\"\n+---\n+\n+# Deep Research Strategy: Global Modes Utilization\n+\n+## 1. OVERVIEW\n+\n+### Purpose\n+Determine how the existing 1,290-style library should become useful across the sk-design hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport without flattening mode authority or duplicating the phase-001 retrieval architecture.\n+\n+## 2. TOPIC\n+\n+How should the 1,290-style design-token library at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus `design-mcp-open-design`, with per-mode integration shapes, out-of-the-box extensions, and rough build costs?\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n+\n+- [ ] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n+- [ ] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?\n+- [ ] How should `design-foundations` turn captured token axes and relationships into safe starting systems, compatibility maps, and implementation-ready evidence without averaging values or claiming accessibility proof?\n+- [ ] How should `design-motion` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?\n+- [ ] How should `design-audit` and `design-mcp-open-design` use the corpus for drift, similarity, provenance, comparison, and transport grounding; which cross-mode ideas should ship first at what rough cost?\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+\n+## 4. NON-GOALS\n+\n+- Do not design or implement the retrieval engine already settled by phase 001.\n+- Do not research `design-md-generator`; phase 002 owns that mode.\n+- Do not modify the corpus, mode contracts, hub, transport, spec packet, databases, or any path outside this detached lineage.\n+- Do not turn the corpus into a pick-a-vibe menu, preset catalog, or source for unreviewed exact copying.\n+\n+## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n+\n+- Legal convergence requires evidence-backed answers for all five key questions.\n+- The synthesis must provide a concrete integration shape for the hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport.\n+- Every recommended integration must identify authority boundaries, proof behavior, failure/fallback behavior, dependencies, and a rough build cost.\n+- At least three smart or out-of-the-box ideas beyond query/cards/hydration must survive contract and risk analysis.\n+- Stop at 10 iterations even if novelty remains.\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n+\n+[None yet]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+## 7. WHAT WORKED\n+\n+[First iteration pending]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+## 8. WHAT FAILED\n+\n+[First iteration pending]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n+\n+[None yet]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n+\n+[None yet]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n+## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n+\n+- Completed pivots: 0\n+- Failed pivots: 0\n+- Audited overrides: 0\n+- Saturated: none yet\n+- Pivot lineage: none yet\n+- Remaining frontier: per-mode integration shapes and cross-mode extensions\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n+\n+[None yet]\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n+\n+Establish the current-contract gap map: compare phase 001's settled retrieval/consumption baseline with the hub and five in-scope mode/transport contracts, then identify exactly what still lacks an integration point.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n+\n+## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n+\n+- Phase 001 settled canonical artifacts -> checked manifest -> deterministic eligibility -> optional same-generation lexical ranking -> five candidate cards -> mode-owned selection -> bounded hydration -> `CORPUS_USE_PROOF v1`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:66-145]\n+- The stable phase-001 snapshot contained 1,290 complete style bundles. Each bundle separates coherent rationale (`DESIGN.md`), structured tokens (`design-tokens.json`), provenance (`source.md`), implementation mappings, and extraction-debug evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:37-64]\n+- The hub is routing-only and must gather intake, show a visible route/proof plan, preserve smallest-useful-mode selection, and keep transports subordinate to judgment modes. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:155-184]\n+- Interface owns distinctive direction, one justified risk, anti-default critique, register/dials, a context manifest, mechanical preflight, and sk-code handoff. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:14-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:169-209]\n+- Foundations owns role-based static systems and downstream-verifiable token handoffs, but remains read-only and cannot claim deterministic checks ran. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:13-46] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:111-156]\n+- Motion owns the restraint gate, temporal purpose, pattern cards, reduced-motion paths, and implementation mechanism boundaries. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:13-47] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:260-300]\n+- Audit owns evidence labels, severity-ranked findings, a five-dimension score, owner mapping, and the never-fixes boundary. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:13-50] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:136-193]\n+- Open Design is a transport only. Design-bearing reads and every run require prior `sk-design` judgment; live content must not be cached into the repo. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:16-24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:123-139]\n+- `resource-map.md` is absent from the target phase; skip the incoming coverage-map gate.\n+- Spec Kit Memory startup retrieval timed out, so phase 001 and canonical packet/code sources are the continuity authority for this lineage.\n+\n+### Bounded Context Snapshot\n+\n+- Source pointers: in-scope hub/mode `SKILL.md` files, `mode-registry.json`, phase-001 `research.md`, style `_manifest.json`, and representative style bundles.\n+- Reuse candidates: phase-001 candidate-card, hydration, authority, provenance, synthesis-ownership, and proof contracts.\n+- Integration points: manager intake and context manifest; interface Design Read and critique; foundations token starter/handoff; motion restraint/pattern cards; audit worksheet/report; Open Design design-system READ/RUN gates.\n+- Constraints: md-generator excluded, no implementation, no corpus mutation, and all workflow writes confined to this lineage directory.\n+\n+## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n+\n+- Max iterations: 10\n+- Minimum iterations: 3\n+- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n+- Stop policy: legal convergence or max iterations, whichever comes first\n+- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n+- Progressive synthesis: true\n+- Target packet: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization`\n+- Detached lineage: `fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni`\n+- Canonical synthesis: `research.md` in this lineage directory\n*** Add File: .opencode/sp