{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784378606643,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YxfgvPd2Lij455WjA31AMNnS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Research Strategy: global sk-design styles utilization\"\n3: description: \"Detached-lineage strategy for mode-specific utilization of the 1,290-style corpus beyond the baseline retrieval pipeline.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Strategy: Global Modes Utilization\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: ### Purpose\n11: Determine how the existing 1,290-style library should become useful across the sk-design hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport without flattening mode authority or duplicating the phase-001 retrieval architecture.\n12: \n13: ## 2. TOPIC\n14: \n15: How should the 1,290-style design-token library at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus `design-mcp-open-design`, with per-mode integration shapes, out-of-the-box extensions, and rough build costs?\n16: \n17: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n18: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n19: - [x] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n20: - [ ] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?\n21: - [ ] How should `design-foundations` turn captured token axes and relationships into safe starting systems, compatibility maps, and implementation-ready evidence without averaging values or claiming accessibility proof?\n22: - [ ] How should `design-motion` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?\n23: - [ ] How should `design-audit` and `design-mcp-open-design` use the corpus for drift, similarity, provenance, comparison, and transport grounding; which cross-mode ideas should ship first at what rough cost?\n24: \n25: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n26: \n27: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n28: \n29: - Do not design or implement the retrieval engine already settled by phase 001.\n30: - Do not research `design-md-generator`; phase 002 owns that mode.\n31: - Do not modify the corpus, mode contracts, hub, transport, spec packet, databases, or any path outside this detached lineage.\n32: - Do not turn the corpus into a pick-a-vibe menu, preset catalog, or source for unreviewed exact copying.\n33: \n34: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n35: \n36: - Legal convergence requires evidence-backed answers for all five key questions.\n37: - The synthesis must provide a concrete integration shape for the hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport.\n38: - Every recommended integration must identify authority boundaries, proof behavior, failure/fallback behavior, dependencies, and a rough build cost.\n39: - At least three smart or out-of-the-box ideas beyond query/cards/hydration must survive contract and risk analysis.\n40: - Stop at 10 iterations even if novelty remains.\n41: \n42: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n43: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n44: - What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n45: \n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n47: \n48: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n49: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n50: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n51: - comparing the phase-001 consumer table directly with each mode's current context, proof, and handoff hooks exposed missing insertion points without reopening retrieval architecture. (iteration 1)\n52: \n53: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n56: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n57: - mode contracts alone cannot validate the proposed schemas against representative corpus bundles; that evidence belongs in focused mode iterations. (iteration 1)\n58: \n59: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n62: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n63: ### **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n64: - What was tried: **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152]\n65: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n66: - Do NOT retry: **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152]\n67: \n68: ### **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n69: - What was tried: **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128]\n70: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n71: - Do NOT retry: **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128]\n72: \n73: ### **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n74: - What was tried: **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184]\n75: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n76: - Do NOT retry: **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184]\n77: \n78: ### **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n79: - What was tried: **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184]\n80: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n81: - Do NOT retry: **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184]\n82: \n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n84: \n85: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n86: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n87: - **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152] (iteration 1)\n88: - **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128] (iteration 1)\n89: - **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184] (iteration 1)\n90: - **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184] (iteration 1)\n91: \n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n93: \n94: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n95: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n96: - Completed pivots: 0\n97: - Failed pivots: 0\n98: - Audited overrides: 0\n99: - Saturated: none yet\n100: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n101: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n102: \n103: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n104: \n105: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n106: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n107: - How should `design-interface` use coherent exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a chooser or copy path? (iteration 1)\n108: - How should `design-foundations` turn token axes and relationships into safe starting systems and compatibility maps without averaging or false proof? (iteration 1)\n109: - How should `design-motion` use sparse temporal evidence and safe no-motion inference under its restraint gate? (iteration 1)\n110: - How should `design-audit` and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation? (iteration 1)\n111: \n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n113: \n114: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n115: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n116: How should `design-audit` and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation?\n117: \n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n119: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n120: \n121: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n122: \n123: - Phase 001 settled canonical artifacts -> checked manifest -> deterministic eligibility -> optional same-generation lexical ranking -> five candidate cards -> mode-owned selection -> bounded hydration -> `CORPUS_USE_PROOF v1`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:66-145]\n124: - The stable phase-001 snapshot contained 1,290 complete style bundles. Each bundle separates coherent rationale (`DESIGN.md`), structured tokens (`design-tokens.json`), provenance (`source.md`), implementation mappings, and extraction-debug evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:37-64]\n125: - The hub is routing-only and must gather intake, show a visible route/proof plan, preserve smallest-useful-mode selection, and keep transports subordinate to judgment modes. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:155-184]\n126: - Interface owns distinctive direction, one justified risk, anti-default critique, register/dials, a context manifest, mechanical preflight, and sk-code handoff. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:14-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:169-209]\n127: - Foundations owns role-based static systems and downstream-verifiable token handoffs, but remains read-only and cannot claim deterministic checks ran. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:13-46] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:111-156]\n128: - Motion owns the restraint gate, temporal purpose, pattern cards, reduced-motion paths, and implementation mechanism boundaries. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:13-47] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:260-300]\n129: - Audit owns evidence labels, severity-ranked findings, a five-dimension score, owner mapping, and the never-fixes boundary. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:13-50] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:136-193]\n130: - Open Design is a transport only. Design-bearing reads and every run require prior `sk-design` judgment; live content must not be cached into the repo. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:16-24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:123-139]\n131: - `resource-map.md` is absent from the target phase; skip the incoming coverage-map gate.\n132: - Spec Kit Memory startup retrieval timed out, so phase 001 and canonical packet/code sources are the continuity authority for this lineage.\n133: \n134: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n135: \n136: - Source pointers: in-scope hub/mode `SKILL.md` files, `mode-registry.json`, phase-001 `research.md`, style `_manifest.json`, and representative style bundles.\n137: - Reuse candidates: phase-001 candidate-card, hydration, authority, provenance, synthesis-ownership, and proof contracts.\n138: - Integration points: manager intake and context manifest; interface Design Read and critique; foundations token starter/handoff; motion restraint/pattern cards; audit worksheet/report; Open Design design-system READ/RUN gates.\n139: - Constraints: md-generator excluded, no implementation, no corpus mutation, and all workflow writes confined to this lineage directory.\n140: \n141: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n142: \n143: - Max iterations: 10\n144: - Minimum iterations: 3\n145: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n146: - Stop policy: legal convergence or max iterations, whichever comes first\n147: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n148: - Progressive synthesis: true\n149: - Target packet: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization`\n150: - Detached lineage: `fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni`\n151: - Canonical synthesis: `research.md` in this lineage directory\n\n(End of file - total 151 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy: global sk-design styles utilization\"\ndescription: \"Detached-lineage strategy for mode-specific utilization of the 1,290-style corpus beyond the baseline retrieval pipeline.\"\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy: Global Modes Utilization\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nDetermine how the existing 1,290-style library should become useful across the sk-design hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport without flattening mode authority or duplicating the phase-001 retrieval architecture.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nHow should the 1,290-style design-token library at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus `design-mcp-open-design`, with per-mode integration shapes, out-of-the-box extensions, and rough build costs?\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n- [ ] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy: global sk-design styles utilization\"\ndescription: \"Detached-lineage strategy for mode-specific utilization of the 1,290-style corpus beyond the baseline retrieval pipeline.\"\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy: Global Modes Utilization\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nDetermine how the existing 1,290-style library should become useful across the sk-design hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport without flattening mode authority or duplicating the phase-001 retrieval architecture.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nHow should the 1,290-style design-token library at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus `design-mcp-open-design`, with per-mode integration shapes, out-of-the-box extensions, and rough build costs?\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n- [ ] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?\n- [ ] How should `design-foundations` turn captured token axes and relationships into safe starting systems, compatibility maps, and implementation-ready evidence without averaging values or claiming accessibility proof?\n- [ ] How should `design-motion` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?\n- [ ] How should `design-audit` and `design-mcp-open-design` use the corpus for drift, similarity, provenance, comparison, and transport grounding; which cross-mode ideas should ship first at what rough cost?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not design or implement the retrieval engine already settled by phase 001.\n- Do not research `design-md-generator`; phase 002 owns that mode.\n- Do not modify the corpus, mode contracts, hub, transport, spec packet, databases, or any path outside this detached lineage.\n- Do not turn the corpus into a pick-a-vibe menu, preset catalog, or source for unreviewed exact copying.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Legal convergence requires evidence-backed answers for all five key questions.\n- The synthesis must provide a concrete integration shape for the hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport.\n- Every recommended integration must identify authority boundaries, proof behavior, failure/fallback behavior, dependencies, and a rough build cost.\n- At least three smart or out-of-the-box ideas beyond query/cards/hydration must survive contract and risk analysis.\n- Stop at 10 iterations even if novelty remains.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- comparing the phase-001 consumer table directly with each mode's current context, proof, and handoff hooks exposed missing insertion points without reopening retrieval architecture. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- mode contracts alone cannot validate the proposed schemas against representative corpus bundles; that evidence belongs in focused mode iterations. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n### **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152]\n\n### **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128]\n\n### **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184]\n\n### **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184] -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184]\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152] (iteration 1)\n- **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128] (iteration 1)\n- **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184] (iteration 1)\n- **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184] (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- How should `design-interface` use coherent exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a chooser or copy path? (iteration 1)\n- How should `design-foundations` turn token axes and relationships into safe starting systems and compatibility maps without averaging or false proof? (iteration 1)\n- How should `design-motion` use sparse temporal evidence and safe no-motion inference under its restraint gate? (iteration 1)\n- How should `design-audit` and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation? (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nHow should `design-audit` and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Phase 001 settled canonical artifacts -> checked manifest -> deterministic eligibility -> optional same-generation lexical ranking -> five candidate cards -> mode-owned selection -> bounded hydration -> `CORPUS_USE_PROOF v1`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:66-145]\n- The stable phase-001 snapshot contained 1,290 complete style bundles. Each bundle separates coherent rationale (`DESIGN.md`), structured tokens (`design-tokens.json`), provenance (`source.md`), implementation mappings, and extraction-debug evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:37-64]\n- The hub is routing-only and must gather intake, show a visible route/proof plan, preserve smallest-useful-mode selection, and keep transports subordinate to judgment modes. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:155-184]\n- Interface owns distinctive direction, one justified risk, anti-default critique, register/dials, a context manifest, mechanical preflight, and sk-code handoff. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:14-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:169-209]\n- Foundations owns role-based static systems and downstream-verifiable token handoffs, but remains read-only and cannot claim deterministic checks ran. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:13-46] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:111-156]\n- Motion owns the restraint gate, temporal purpose, pattern cards, reduced-motion paths, and implementation mechanism boundaries. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:13-47] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:260-300]\n- Audit owns evidence labels, severity-ranked findings, a five-dimension score, owner mapping, and the never-fixes boundary. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:13-50] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md:136-193]\n- Open Design is a transport only. Design-bearing reads and every run require prior `sk-design` judgment; live content must not be cached into the repo. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:16-24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:123-139]\n- `resource-map.md` is absent from the target phase; skip the incoming coverage-map gate.\n- Spec Kit Memory startup retrieval timed out, so phase 001 and canonical packet/code sources are the continuity authority for this lineage.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\n- Source pointers: in-scope hub/mode `SKILL.md` files, `mode-registry.json`, phase-001 `research.md`, style `_manifest.json`, and representative style bundles.\n- Reuse candidates: phase-001 candidate-card, hydration, authority, provenance, synthesis-ownership, and proof contracts.\n- Integration points: manager intake and context manifest; interface Design Read and critique; foundations token starter/handoff; motion restraint/pattern cards; audit worksheet/report; Open Design design-system READ/RUN gates.\n- Constraints: md-generator excluded, no implementation, no corpus mutation, and all workflow writes confined to this lineage directory.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Minimum iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Stop policy: legal convergence or max iterations, whichever comes first\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Target packet: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization`\n- Detached lineage: `fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni`\n- Canonical synthesis: `research.md` in this lineage directory","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":151,"totalLines":151,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784378606636,"end":1784378606641}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052e2facbb083f8c016a5b74ee7d1481919ae64455b84a28cc"}},"id":"prt_f7540c3e10012cke4eys4CtN04","sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","messageID":"msg_f7540a3d30014LKtq28pbtvbrY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784378606742,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_z9tylSrpIRy2aTXOga6SFJZO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"How should the 1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes plus the design-mcp-open-design transport?\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-18T12:35:15Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/.reducer-spec\",\"targetSpecFolder\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"folder_state\":\"fanout-lineage-isolated\",\"normalized_topic\":\"global utilization of the sk-design styles library across non-md-generator modes and open design\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md\",\"mutation\":\"skipped\",\"reason\":\"Detached li