{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784378631983,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Tgn29WLZBMTtrIo1yydZBLn5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration 2\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 2 of 10\n+Questions: 1/5 answered | Last focus: current-contract gap map\n+Last ratios: N/A -> 0.83 | Stuck count: 0\n+Next focus from reducer: How should design-audit and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation?\n+\n+Research Topic: Global utilization of the 1,290-style sk-design corpus across the hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport, excluding md-generator.\n+\n+## REQUIRED ACTIONS\n+\n+1. Read state, strategy, registry, iteration 1, and the phase-001 synthesis first.\n+2. Inspect audit's evidence-capture, audit-contract, anti-pattern, worksheet/report, and owner-handoff surfaces plus Open Design's live-read/run/parity transport contracts.\n+3. Test concrete audit integration shapes against the distinction between target evidence, corpus comparison evidence, deterministic accessibility/performance proof, severity, and remediation ownership.\n+4. Define the Open Design transport receipt and live-reference handshake, including no-cache, mandatory pairing, generation mismatch, and return-path reconciliation.\n+5. Rank the audit and Open Design ideas by leverage/cost and rule out unsafe similarity, copying, and transport-authority paths.\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+- Narrative output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+- Delta output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- LEAF only; 3-5 research actions; at most 12 tool calls; no subagents or nested loops.\n+- Write only the narrative, append-only state log, and delta paths named above.\n+- Do not use Open Design live tools or trigger a run. Research its checked-in contract only.\n+- Treat the corpus as comparison/reference evidence, never truth about quality, accessibility, intent, or copying.\n+- Scope away from md-generator. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`; label inference.\n+\n+## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n+\n+Produce the three canonical iteration artifacts. The state and delta iteration records must be identical and include `type:\"iteration\"`, `iteration:2`, `run:2`, mode/route proof, novelty fields, status/focus/counts, exact key/answered question arrays, ruled-out directions, sources, timestamp, lineage fields, and executor `{kind:\"cli-opencode\",model:\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",reasoningEffort:null,serviceTier:null}`. The narrative must include Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Dead Ends, Assessment, Reflection, Sources Consulted, and Recommended Next Focus.\n+\n+Answer the combined audit/Open Design key question only if both modes receive a complete operational contract and ship-order recommendation.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,44 @@\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration 2\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 2 of 10\n+Questions: 1/5 answered | Last focus: current-contract gap map\n+Last ratios: N/A -> 0.83 | Stuck count: 0\n+Next focus from reducer: How should design-audit and Open Design operationalize drift, similarity, provenance, and transport grounding, and what should ship first after contract validation?\n+\n+Research Topic: Global utilization of the 1,290-style sk-design corpus across the hub, interface, foundations, motion, audit, and Open Design transport, excluding md-generator.\n+\n+## REQUIRED ACTIONS\n+\n+1. Read state, strategy, registry, iteration 1, and the phase-001 synthesis first.\n+2. Inspect audit's evidence-capture, audit-contract, anti-pattern, worksheet/report, and owner-handoff su