/sol/findings-registry.json\n+- Narrative output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+- Delta output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- LEAF only; 3-5 research actions; at most 12 tool calls; no subagents or nested loops.\n+- Write only the narrative, append-only state log, and delta paths named above.\n+- Do not use Open Design live tools or trigger a run. Research its checked-in contract only.\n+- Treat the corpus as comparison/reference evidence, never truth about quality, accessibility, intent, or copying.\n+- Scope away from md-generator. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`; label inference.\n+\n+## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n+\n+Produce the three canonical iteration artifacts. The state and delta iteration records must be identical and include `type:\"iteration\"`, `iteration:2`, `run:2`, mode/route proof, novelty fields, status/focus/counts, exact key/answered question arrays, ruled-out directions, sources, timestamp, lineage fields, and executor `{kind:\"cli-opencode\",model:\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",reasoningEffort:null,serviceTier:null}`. The narrative must include Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Dead Ends, Assessment, Reflection, Sources Consulted, and Recommended Next Focus.\n+\n+Answer the combined audit/Open Design key question only if both modes receive a complete operational contract and ship-order recommendation.\n","additions":44,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-2.md","time":{"start":1784378631975,"end":1784378631980}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f88e535e0b1dec6016a5b74f70d6c81918