{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784380440390,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_W2W5vYSnuh2VKFDKnLjQcggp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-6.md\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration 6\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 6 of 10\n+Questions: 4/5 answered | Last focus: foundations token-source contract\n+Ratios: 0.83 -> 0.92 -> 0.92 -> 0.70 -> 0.92 | Stuck count: 0\n+Only unresolved canonical question: motion.\n+\n+Focus Area: Define `design-motion`'s corpus-evidence eligibility, no-motion baseline, restraint-gated exemplar, and handoff contract.\n+\n+## REQUIRED ACTIONS\n+\n+1. Read state, strategy, registry, prior iterations, phase-001 synthesis, and its most relevant motion evidence/holdout iteration first.\n+2. Inspect motion's restraint, strategy, micro-interaction, performance/reduced-motion, pattern-card, and handoff contracts.\n+3. Inspect a bounded set of corpus styles with true temporal evidence and hard negatives where temporal words are incidental or animation is prohibited. Distinguish measured/declared motion from static aesthetic similarity.\n+4. Specify eligibility scoring, zero-hydration/no-motion behavior, purpose/material/state extraction, reduced-motion limitations, proof/handoff fields, refusal/fallback rules, and rough cost.\n+5. Test beyond-baseline ideas: negative motion baselines, purpose-first motion grammar, interaction-state archetype retrieval, temporal counterexamples, and drift checks that never bypass the restraint gate.\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+- Narrative output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-006.md\n+- Delta output: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deltas/iter-006.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- LEAF only; 3-5 actions; max 12 tool calls; no subagents/nested loops.\n+- Write only the three canonical iteration artifacts.\n+- Run the motion restraint gate conceptually before corpus retrieval. High-frequency, keyboard-driven, purposeless, or reduced-motion-unsafe behavior stays instant.\n+- Static similarity and incidental temporal vocabulary are not motion evidence. Corpus evidence cannot prove performance or accessibility.\n+- Do not copy source-specific timings or signature choreography without target reason and rights evidence.\n+- md-generator excluded. Cite every finding and label inference.\n+\n+## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n+\n+Produce canonical artifacts for iteration/run 6 with identical state/delta iteration records, route proof, novelty, focus/status/counts, exact question arrays, ruled-out directions, sources, timestamp, session/generation, and executor `{kind:\"cli-opencode\",model:\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",reasoningEffort:null,serviceTier:null}`.\n+\n+If fully closed, `answeredQuestions` MUST contain exactly: `How should \\`design-motion\\` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?`\n+\n+Include all standard narrative sections. Because all key questions may then be answered, recommend a synthesis-readiness/quality-guard closure pass rather than immediate implementation.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-6.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-6.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-6.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-6.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,47 @@\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration 6\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 6 of 10\n+Questions: 4/5 answered | Last focus: foundations token-source contract\n+Ratios: 0.83 -> 0.92 -> 0.92 -> 0.70 -> 0.92 | Stuck count: 0\n+Only unresolved canonical question: motion.\n+\n+Focus Area: Define `design-motion`'s corpus-evidence eligibility, no-motion baseline, restraint-gated exemplar, and handoff contract.\n+\n+## REQUIRED ACTIONS\n+\n+1. Read state, strategy, registry, prior iterations, phase-001 synthesis, and its most relevant motion evidence/holdout iteration first.\n+2. Inspect motion's restraint, strategy, micro-interaction, perform