{"type":"text","timestamp":1784380891010,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"id":"prt_f756380e3001w971eRgnmY4JZW","messageID":"msg_f7563680e001aS6BJizV2rXc2J","sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","type":"text","text":"All five canonical questions now have evidence after six iterations. I’m evaluating the legal-stop quality gates next: source diversity, per-mode coverage, evidence strength, negative knowledge, rough-cost completeness, and synthesis readiness.","time":{"start":1784380883171,"end":1784380891009},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0dcb9415bb40dbcf016a5b7dd317408191acb14223c4ec288b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784380891213,"sessionID":"ses_08acc7a6affeS35KntG0P1wx2Z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qbCizCAB9oBtL3RaV2EGIT1K","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated reducer view over the research packet.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n7: \n8: Auto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n9: \n10: <!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n11: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n12: \n13: Reducer-generated observability surface for the active research packet.\n14: \n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n16: <!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n17: ## 2. STATUS\n18: - Topic: How should the 1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ be utilized globally across the sk-design hub and its non-md-generator modes (design-interface, design-foundations, design-motion, design-audit) plus the design-mcp-open-design transport -- as shared reference material, retrieval-backed exemplars, foundation token sources, and audit/drift baselines? Inspect each mode's real contract and give a per-mode integration shape. Build on ../001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md but scope away from md-generator (owned by phase 002). Emphasize smart integrations and out-of-the-box ideas beyond the 001 baseline retrieval pipeline, each with rough build cost.\n19: - Started: 2026-07-18T12:35:15Z\n20: - Status: INITIALIZED\n21: - Iteration: 6 of 10\n22: - Session ID: fanout-sol-1784377737893-mlzyni\n23: - Parent Session: none\n24: - Lifecycle Mode: new\n25: - Generation: 1\n26: - continuedFromRun: none\n27: \n28: <!-- /ANCHOR:status -->\n29: <!-- ANCHOR:progress -->\n30: ## 3. PROGRESS\n31: \n32: | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n33: |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n34: | 1 | Establish the current-contract gap map for global corpus utilization across the hub and five in-scope consumers | architecture | 0.83 | 6 | complete |\n35: | 2 | Operationalize audit drift/similarity/provenance evidence and Open Design transport grounding, then rank ship order | audit-transport-contracts | 0.92 | 6 | complete |\n36: | 3 | Define and validate design-interface's relational exemplar contract for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and source-aware handoff | interface-relational-exemplars | 0.92 | 6 | complete |\n37: | 4 | Reconcile the canonical audit/Open Design question and re-validate comparison, grounding, fixture, ship-order, and cost boundaries | audit-transport-reconciliation | 0.70 | 5 | complete |\n38: | 5 | Define and validate design-foundations' axis-compatibility and safe token-source contract | foundations-contract | 0.92 | 6 | complete |\n39: | 6 | Define design-motion corpus-evidence eligibility, no-motion baseline, restraint-gated exemplar, proof, fallback, and handoff contracts | motion-contract | 0.93 | 6 | complete |\n40: \n41: - iterationsCompleted: 6\n42: - keyFindings: 35\n43: - openQuestions: 0\n44: - resolvedQuestions: 5\n45: \n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n47: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n48: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n49: - Answered: 5/5\n50: - [x] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n51: - [x] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?\n52: - [x] How should `design-foundations` turn captured token axes and relationships into safe starting systems, compatibility maps, and implementation-ready evidence without averaging values or claiming accessibility proof?\n53: - [x] How should `design-motion` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?\n54: - [x] How should `design-audit` and `design-mcp-open-design` use the corpus for drift, similarity, provenance, comparison, and transport grounding; which cross-mode ideas should ship first at what rough cost?\n55: \n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n57: <!-- ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n58: ## Uncovered Questions\n59: - Count: 0\n60: - None\n61: \n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n63: <!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n64: ## 5. TREND\n65: - newInfoRatio sparkline: ▅▆▆▇████▇▅▃▂▂▄▆▇████\n66: - score sparkline: ▅▆▆▇████▇▅▃▂▂▄▆▇████\n67: - Last 3 ratios: 0.70 -> 0.92 -> 0.93\n68: - Stuck count: 0\n69: - Guard violations: none recorded by the reducer pass\n70: - convergenceScore: 0.93\n71: - coverageBySources: {\"code\":172}\n72: - Advisory events: none\n73: \n74: <!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n75: <!-- ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n76: ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n77: - **Caching corpus/Open Design payloads into the repository:** rejected because Open Design content must be read live and not vendored. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:145-152] (iteration 1)\n78: - **Corpus-driven routing:** rejected because routing follows user intent and the registry; the corpus is consulted only after a mode is selected. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:42-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:98-128] (iteration 1)\n79: - **Hub-local taste policy:** rejected because the hub is registry/routing-only and the selected mode owns judgment. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:40-71] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:172-184] (iteration 1)\n80: - **Mode flattening into one corpus consumer:** rejected because current contracts preserve distinct interface, foundations, motion, and audit authorities and proof obligations. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:166-184] (iteration 1)\n81: - **Cached or stale payload fallback:** design content stays live, while corpus hydration refuses generation mismatch. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md:143-150] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:130-132] (iteration 2)\n82: - **Raw exact-value or signature-motif transfer:** provenance does not authorize copying, and phase 001 forbids unreviewed source-specific reuse under unknown rights. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:172-191] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:350-356] (iteration 2)\n83: - **Similarity as severity, quality, or copying proof:** nearest-neighbor distance and corpus prevalence lack target impact and independent copying evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit_contract.md:36-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:172-191] (iteration 2)\n84: - **Transport authority or one-shot completion:** Open Design is transport-only, and turn 1 yields a discovery form with zero files. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md:48-54] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md:154-170] (iteration 2)\n85: - **Contrast as a second identity source:** rejected because Kobu and 19-86 have incompatible imagery, typography, rhythm, and signature locks; combining them yields an unowned third identity. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/kobu/DESIGN.md:1-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/19-86/DESIGN.md:1-31] (iteration 3)\n86: - **Raw corpus payload in the implementation handoff:** rejected because handoff ownership is accepted design decisions and constraints, while unknown rights prohibit exact source-specific reuse. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/sk_code_handoff.md:23-35] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:350-364] (iteration 3)\n87: - **Scalar distance or genericness score:** rejected because it cannot encode authority, target reason, or whether a difference should be preserved, transformed, or refused. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:174-189] [INFERENCE: per-axis relational states are reviewable where a scalar is not] (iteration 3)\n88: - **Three equal exemplar choices:** rejected because equal presentation becomes a style chooser and erases mode-owned role semantics. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/manual_testing_playbook/real_ui_loop/reuse_before_generate_with_design_system.md:31-44] [INFERENCE: anchor/contrast/rejection roles must remain unequal] (iteration 3)\n89: - Reopening live Open Design evidence was ruled out because the dispatch requires checked-in-contract validation and explicitly forbids Open Design live tools. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/prompts/iteration-4.md:31-38] (iteration 4)\n90: - Treating comparison evidence as target evidence, severity, quality, accessibility/performance proof, or copying proof remains invalid. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit_contract.md:36-138] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:134-145] (iteration 4)\n91: - Treating the grounding receipt as mutation approval, transport acceptance, a cache license, or one-shot completion remains invalid. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:127-154] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md:143-170] (iteration 4)\n92: - **Coarse independent-axis ownership without cross-axis edge reconciliation:** Kobu and 19-86 couple type, spacing, composition, imagery, and color, so a key-name boundary is not a semantic ownership boundary. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/kobu/DESIGN.md:1-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/19-86/DESIGN.md:1-24] [INFERENCE: compatibility requires typed dependency edges] (iteration 5)\n93: - **Corpus provenance or extracted values as accessibility, contrast, reuse-rights, or extraction-truth proof:** target pairs and downstream deterministic runs remain required. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/assets/contrast_pair_inventory.md:15-55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:350-364] (iteration 5)\n94: - **Directly filling the target token starter from captured raw values:** source spacing, typography, naming, and surface shapes do not satisfy the target scaffold's register, role, baseline, dark-mode, or verification contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/assets/token_starter.md:30-145] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/kobu/DESIGN.md:44-95] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/19-86/DESIGN.md:26-62] (iteration 5)\n95: - **Top-level axis co-presence as compatibility proof:** both fixtures expose color/type/spacing while their role relationships and identity constraints conflict. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/kobu/design-tokens.json:1-318] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/19-86/design-tokens.json:1-89] (iteration 5)\n96: - Promote “axis-key presence equals compatibility” as an exhausted direction: the two real bundles falsify it without requiring a corpus crawl. Future work should test typed relationship edges, not add more sources to that coarse heuristic. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/kobu/design-tokens.json:1-318] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/19-86/design-tokens.json:1-89] [INFERENCE: additional samples cannot repair a semantically under-specified compatibility test] (iteration 5)\n97: - **Copying source timings, easing signatures, continuous loops, or signature choreography without target reason and rights evidence:** source provenance and descriptive rationale do not establish reuse authority. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:350-364] (iteration 6)\n98: - **Corpus drift checks before or instead of the restraint gate:** comparison begins only after a target motion decision and cannot manufacture purpose. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:262-275] (iteration 6)\n99: - **Corpus evidence as reduced-motion accessibility or performance proof:** only target behavior and measurement can verify these claims. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/performance_reduced_motion.md:94-100] (iteration 6)\n100: - **Static similarity or absent motion prose as proof that the target should not animate:** absence proves only no corpus temporal authority; target no-motion requires the restraint gate or independent target evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/animation_decision_framework.md:92-101] [INFERENCE: evidence absence and target decision have different authority] (iteration 6)\n101: - **Temporal-word frequency or BM25-only eligibility:** `099-supply` and `relate` rank for requested words while explicitly negating requested choreography. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-008.md:31-37] (iteration 6)\n102: - Promote “static corpus absence determines no-motion” as exhausted: no-motion is a restraint-gate result, while an empty temporal result is a safe zero-hydration fallback. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/animation_decision_framework.md:92-101] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:136-145] (iteration 6)\n103: - Promote “temporal vocabulary implies motion eligibility” as exhausted: positive polarity and purpose/state composition are mandatory because explicit negations otherwise score as matches. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-008.md:31-37] (iteration 6)\n104: \n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:dead-ends -->\n106: <!-- ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n107: ## 6A. DIVERGENT PIVOTS\n108: - Completed pivots: 0\n109: - Failed pivots: 0\n110: - Audited overrides: 0\n111: - Saturated: none yet\n112: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n113: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n114: \n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergent-pivots -->\n116: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n117: ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n118: [All tracked questions are resolved]\n119: \n120: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n121: <!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n122: ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n123: - None active beyond normal research uncertainty.\n124: \n125: <!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n126: <!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n127: ## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\n128: No blocked-stop events recorded.\n129: \n130: <!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n131: <!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n132: ## 10. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n133: - graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n134: - graphDecision: [Not recorded]\n