 and validate design-foundations' axis-compatibility and safe token-source contract | foundations-contract | 0.92 | 6 | complete |\n| 6 | Define design-motion corpus-evidence eligibility, no-motion baseline, restraint-gated exemplar, proof, fallback, and handoff contracts | motion-contract | 0.93 | 6 | complete |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: 6\n- keyFindings: 35\n- openQuestions: 0\n- resolvedQuestions: 5\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n- Answered: 5/5\n- [x] What hub-level contract can expose corpus capabilities, task-derived queries, authority order, and proof requirements while keeping the hub routing-only?\n- [x] How should `design-interface` use coherent style exemplars for grounding, anti-default critique, variation diversity, and handoff without becoming a style chooser or copy path?\n- [x] How should `design-foundations` turn captured token axes and relationships into safe starting systems, compatibility maps, and implementation-ready evidence without averaging values or claiming accessibility proof?\n- [x] How should `design-motion` discover and use sparse temporal evidence, infer no motion from static styles safely, and build motion-specific exemplars or negative baselines under its restraint gate?\n- [x] How should `design-audit` and `design-mcp-open-design` use the corpus for drift, similarity, provenance, comparison, and transport grounding; which cross-mode ideas should ship first at what rough cost?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n## Uncovered Questions\n- Count: 0\n- None\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n## 5. TREND\n- newInfoRatio sparkline: ▅▆▆▇████▇▅▃▂▂▄▆▇████\n- score sparkline: ▅▆▆▇████▇▅▃▂▂▄▆▇████\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.70 -> 0.92 -> 0.93\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none recorded by the reducer pass\n- convergenceScore: 0.93\n- coverageBySources: {\"code\":172}\n- Advisory events: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:dead-end